    • implementClass

      public static Path implementClass(Class<?> aClass, Path path) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided aClass.

      Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified path directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Parameters:
      aClass - type token to create implementation for.
      path - root directory.
      Returns:
      path to implemented class.
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • generateAllConstructors

      private static String generateAllConstructors(Class<?> aClass) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Generate constructors for basic aClass implementation. If aClass is interface, generate only default constructor. If aClass is class, generate constructors that have same signature like all aClass non-private constructors and passes arguments to super
      Parameters:
      aClass - class in each constructor parameters pass
      Returns:
      String of implementation of constructors
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - throws when aClass have only private constructors
